  "title": "docs(examples): depend on all transitive internal dependencies",
  "body": "\r\n<!--\r\n  Thanks for submitting a pull request!\r\n  Please provide enough information so that others can review your pull request.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Summary**\r\n\r\nThis allows us to make a deep change in the helper, ui components or similar, but still try that out in an example in codesandbox without manually adding that dependency.\r\n\r\n<!--\r\n  Explain the **motivation** for making this change.\r\n  What existing problem does the pull request solve?\r\n  Are there any linked issues?\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Result**\r\n\r\nall local dependencies (including transitive) are explicitly depended upon for examples.\r\n\r\nA visual way to try this out is running the react example and adding a chat. Works with this preview, but not with previous ones.\r\n\r\n<!--\r\n  Demonstrate the code is solid.\r\n  Example: The exact commands you ran and their output,\r\n  screenshots / videos if the pull request changes UI.\r\n-->\r\n",
